                        <p>For entry-level positions, a bachelor's degree in any discipline is typically sufficient, though commerce, economics, or finance backgrounds are preferred. Many banks conduct their own entrance exams (like IBPS for public sector banks). Professional certifications like JAIIB and CAIIB can accelerate career growth. Strong numerical skills, communication abilities, and customer service orientation are essential regardless of educational background.</p>
