                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Public sector banks typically offer better job security, structured pay scales, and comprehensive benefits including pension schemes. Private banks often provide higher starting salaries, performance-based incentives, and faster career progression. Public sector: ₹3-15 LPA with excellent job security. Private sector: ₹4-25+ LPA with performance-linked growth. The choice depends on your priorities regarding security versus growth potential.</p>
